Standard Options
================

   All of the UUCP programs support a few standard options.

@{b}-x type@{ub}
@{b}--debug type@{ub}
     Turn on particular debugging types.  The following types are
     recognized: @{b}abnormal@{ub}, @{b}chat@{ub}, @{b}handshake@{ub}, @{b}uucp-proto@{ub}, @{b}proto@{ub}, @{b}port@{ub},
     @{b}config@{ub}, @{b}spooldir@{ub}, @{b}execute@{ub}, @{b}incoming@{ub}, @{b}outgoing@{ub}.  Not all
     types of debugging are effective for all programs.  See the @{b}debug@{ub}
     configuration command for details (see @{"Debugging Levels" Link "Debugging Levels"}).

     Multiple types may be given, separated by commas, and the @{b}--debug@{ub}
     option may appear multiple times.  A number may also be given,
     which will turn on that many types from the foregoing list; for
     example, @{b}--debug 2@{ub} is equivalent to @{b}--debug abnormal,chat@{ub}.  To turn
     on all types of debugging, use @{b}-x all@{ub}.

     The @{b}uulog@{ub} program uses @{b}-X@{ub} rather than @{b}-x@{ub} to select the debugging
     type; for @{b}uulog@{ub}, @{b}-x@{ub} has a different meaning, for reasons of
     historical compatibility.

@{b}-I file@{ub}
@{b}--config file@{ub}
     Set the main configuration file to use.  See @{"config File" Link "config File"}.  When
     this option is used, the programs will revoke any setuid
     privileges.

@{b}-v@{ub}
@{b}--version@{ub}
     Report version information and exit.

@{b}--help@{ub}
     Print a help message and exit.


@EndNode

